    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-04-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-04-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="511"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d511">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to <persName
                            type="to">Mavroyeni Bey</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-04-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1895</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 9.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Acknowledging the receipt of the note with which
                    you have favored me under to-day’s date, I have the pleasure to inform you that
                    the report of the intended visit of the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">San
                        Francisco</hi> to Smyrna is correct. Having recently visited Jaffa, and gone
                    thence td the Piraeus and Palermo to await her consort, the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Marblehead</hi>, the two ships are about to cruise in the Levant, a part of
                    the Mediterranean which I trust may be more frequently the scene of these
                    friendly visits than has heretofore been practicable.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
